        <div style="margin: 40px 0;">
            <h2 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">What is Retinal Detachment?</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Retinal detachment is a serious condition where the retina separates from the back of the eye. This is a medical emergency that requires immediate attention to prevent permanent vision loss. With prompt treatment, vision can often be restored.</p>

            <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Emergency Warning Signs</h3>
                <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>Sudden increase in floaters or flashes of light</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>A dark curtain or shadow moving across your vision</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>Sudden vision loss in any part of your visual field</span>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle" style="color: #8b0000;"></i>
                        <span>Blurred or distorted vision</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin: 40px 0;">
            <h2 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">Risk Factors</h2>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Age-Related</h3>
                    <p>More common in people over 50, as the vitreous gel naturally changes with age.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Previous Eye Conditions</h3>
                    <p>History of severe myopia, previous eye surgery, or family history of retinal detachment.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Trauma</h3>
                    <p>Eye injury or trauma can increase the risk of retinal detachment.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin: 40px 0;">
            <h2 style="color: #333; margin-bottom: 20px;">Treatment Options</h2>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Laser Surgery (Photocoagulation)</h3>
                    <p>Used for small tears, this procedure creates small burns around the tear to "weld" the retina back in place.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Cryopexy</h3>
                    <p>Freezing treatment that helps reattach the retina and prevent further detachment in cases of small tears.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="background: #f9f9f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <h3 style="color: #8b0000; margin-bottom: 15px;">Vitrectomy</h3>
                    <p>Advanced microsurgery to repair more complex detachments, often combined with gas or silicone oil tamponade.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

